promptInjection:
Use one of these curated palettes via CSS custom properties. DO NOT invent hex colors — modern apps stick to a small palette of named tokens, switched as a unit between themes.

**HOW TO USE:**
```css
:root { /* paste one palette block from below */ }
body { background: var(--color-bg); color: var(--color-fg); }
.btn-primary { background: var(--color-accent); color: var(--color-on-accent); }
.card { background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
```

All palettes meet WCAG AA contrast (4.5:1 for body text) when used as documented (--color-fg on --color-bg, --color-on-accent on --color-accent).

