**RULES:**
- Pick ONE palette block per app — don't mix tokens from different palettes.
- Use semantic names (`var(--color-bg)`) throughout — DO NOT inline hex codes once you've adopted a palette.
- Match palette to genre: dark for dashboards/productivity, retro for arcade games, pastel for kid-facing, warm for cooking, cool for wellness/meditation, neon for cyberpunk/synth.
- Body text MUST be `var(--color-fg)` on `var(--color-bg)` background — that's the contrast-tested pairing.
- For dark-mode toggle: use `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` and supply both LIGHT and DARK blocks under the matching media queries.
